ch.usi.dag.disl.staticcontext

Interface StaticContext

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractStaticContext, BasicBlockStaticContext, BytecodeStaticContext, ClassStaticContext, FieldAccessStaticContext, InstructionStaticContext, InvocationStaticContext, LoopStaticContext, MethodStaticContext, ReflectionStaticContext

    public interface StaticContext

    The static context provides information derived from code's static analysis.

    There is a list of already prepared static contexts.

    • BasicBLockStaticContext - experimental
    • BytecodeStaticContext
    • FieldAccessStaticContext
    • MethodStaticContext
    • LoopStaticContext - experimental

    Every static context class has to implement this interface. All static context methods must adhere to the following convention:

    • a static context method does not have parameters
    • the return value can be only a primitive type or a String
    In addition, a StaticContext implementation has to be thread-safe.
